Subject: Re: [T2] ignition lock questions



On Mon, 26 Nov 2001, William wrote:

> Hello all,
>
> My 71 Westy's ignition lock sometimes depresses about 1/4" into the column.
> In order for me to turn the engine, I have to stick my key in and wiggle out
> the lock. What is going on with this? What do I need to do fix it?

That's how it should work.  Squirt some graphite lube into the cylinder to
make it work easier.

> Also, the passenger side door lock is broken off, and the lock came out of
> the handle...Can locksmith put a new lock in, or should I just buy a handle
> with the lock and have it rekeyed?

If you can get hold of a cylinder, it is easy to rekey, particularly if
you have the broken lock cylinder.  Just swap the wafers and you're done!

George Lyle

